# Allowlist build context: exclude EVERYTHING, then re-include only what the
# demo image needs. The Dockerfile does `COPY . .`, so a blocklist here would
# silently bake private files (real *.local.json profiles, bags, private_eval/,
# internal notes) into image layers pushed to a registry. CI enforces that this
# file starts with '*' and that no re-include resurrects a private path.
*

!backend/
!tools/
!incident/
!specs/
!profiles/
!requirements.txt

# Re-excludes inside the allowed directories (later rules win in dockerignore):
# local-only, generated, or internal files that live under re-included paths.
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.local.json
**/*.key
backend/static/
backend/interactions_client.py
backend/interactions_check.py
backend/frontend/index_verified.html
